{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17602432","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17602432"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T12:25:53+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T12:25:53+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15699"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"15699","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/15699"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.66,0.13,0.03,0.06,0.13]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"8390"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"71448"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"8390","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/8390"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15699"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"56957"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"4"},{"type":"tags","id":"22"},{"type":"tags","id":"25"},{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"1343"},{"type":"tags","id":"2173"},{"type":"tags","id":"3101"},{"type":"tags","id":"4929"},{"type":"tags","id":"4935"},{"type":"tags","id":"4942"},{"type":"tags","id":"4947"},{"type":"tags","id":"4950"},{"type":"tags","id":"5247"},{"type":"tags","id":"5320"},{"type":"tags","id":"7601"},{"type":"tags","id":"10586"},{"type":"tags","id":"10636"},{"type":"tags","id":"11059"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"20215"},{"type":"contributions","id":"20220"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"71448","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/71448"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EA 52-year-old woman presents with severe menopausal symptoms including hot flushes, night sweats, and mood changes. You are considering hormone replacement therapy.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following is the correct hormone therapy based on uterine status?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Oestrogen alone if hysterectomy, combined therapy if uterus present","Combined therapy if hysterectomy, oestrogen alone if uterus present","Oestrogen alone regardless of uterine status","Combined therapy if hysterectomy, progesterone alone if uterus present","Progesterone alone if hysterectomy, combined therapy if uterus present"],"correctOptions":[0],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe correct approach to menopausal hormone therapy depends on whether the woman has an intact uterus. \u003Cstrong\u003EOestrogen alone\u003C/strong\u003E is appropriate for women who have had a hysterectomy since there is no risk of endometrial hyperplasia. However, women with an intact uterus must receive \u003Cstrong\u003Ecombined therapy\u003C/strong\u003E (oestrogen plus progesterone) to prevent endometrial hyperplasia.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EUsing \u003Cstrong\u003Eoestrogen alone regardless of uterine status\u003C/strong\u003E would put women with an intact uterus at risk of endometrial hyperplasia and cancer. This occurs as oestrogen causes stimulation of endometrium, whereas the addition of progesterone counterbalances these effects. \u003Cstrong\u003ECombined therapy if hysterectomy\u003C/strong\u003E unnecessarily exposes women to progesterone when they don\u0027t need it. Using \u003Cstrong\u003Eprogesterone alone\u003C/strong\u003E would not adequately treat menopausal symptoms as oestrogen is the primary hormone needed for symptom relief.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Women with an intact uterus require both oestrogen and progesterone for menopausal hormone therapy to prevent endometrial hyperplasia","Women who have had a hysterectomy only require oestrogen replacement therapy"],"references":["Okeke T, Anyaehie U, Ezenyeaku C. Premature menopause. Ann Med Health Sci Res. 2013 Jan;3(1):90-5. doi: 10.4103/2141-9248.109458. PMID: 23634337; PMCID: PMC3634232","Magraith K, Jang C. Management of menopause. Aust Prescr. 2023 Oct;46(3):48-53. doi: 10.18773/austprescr.2023.014. PMID: 38053812; PMCID: PMC10665088","Santoro N, Epperson CN, Mathews SB. Menopausal Symptoms and Their Management. Endocrinol Metab Clin North Am. 2015 Sep;44(3):497-515. doi: 10.1016/j.ecl.2015.05.001. PMID: 26316239; PMCID: PMC4890704","Hawkins SM, Matzuk MM. The menstrual cycle: basic biology. Ann N Y Acad Sci. 2008;1135:10-8. doi: 10.1196/annals.1429.018. PMID: 18574203; PMCID: PMC2913133","Evans, T. J., \u0026 Ganjam, V. K. (2017). Reproductive anatomy and physiology. In Reproductive and Developmental Toxicology (pp. 7-37). Academic Press","Melmed, S., Polonsky, K. S., Larsen, P. R., \u0026 Kronenberg, H. M. (2015). Williams textbook of endocrinology E-Book. Elsevier Health Sciences"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"56957"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15699"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"56957","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/56957"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2024-12-18T16:54:33+10:30","updatedAt":"2024-12-18T16:55:00+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"8390"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"71448"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"4","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/4"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83c\udf6c","name":"Endocrinology","synonyms":[],"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":"2024-11-21T09:49:43+10:30"},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"1"}},"heading":{"data":{"type":"tagHeadings","id":"1"}}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"22","links":{"self":"https://app.emed